          <type><ref refid="retained__mem_8h_1a36713c339c3c5ec6d6bd481480bdb6f9" kindref="member">size_t</ref></type>
          <declname>num_param</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Add streams to a unicast group as a unicast client. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function can be used to add additional streams to a <ref refid="structbt__bap__unicast__group" kindref="compound">bt_bap_unicast_group</ref>.</para>
<para>This can be called at any time before any of the streams in the group has been started (see <ref refid="structbt__bap__stream__ops_1a7f595e37d40b94510bf09c1f82b479f3" kindref="member">bt_bap_stream_ops.started()</ref>). This can also be called after the streams have been stopped (see <ref refid="structbt__bap__stream__ops_1ab50ea295069a2cd1ab6f4353052262f5" kindref="member">bt_bap_stream_ops.stopped()</ref>).</para>
<para>Once a stream has been added to a unicast group, it cannot be removed. To remove a stream from a group, the group must be deleted with <ref refid="group__bt__bap__unicast__client_1ga34dbdce6133f8366df453ec937fb47d2" kindref="member">bt_bap_unicast_group_delete()</ref>, but this will require all streams in the group to be released first.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>unicast_group</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the unicast group </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>params</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Array of stream parameters with streams being added to the group. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>num_param</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of parameters in <computeroutput>params</computeroutput>.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 in case of success or negative value in case of error. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
